Swicy™ Chicken Tenders Ingredients: • 1 lb (450g) chicken tenders • 1 1/2 cups Lay's Sweet and Spicy Honey Flavored Potato Chips, crushed finely • 1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs • 1 teaspoon smoked paprika • 1 teaspoon garlic powder • 1 teaspoon onion powder • 1 teaspoon cayenne powder • Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste • 2 large eggs • 1 tablespoon milk • 1/2 cup all-purpose flour • Vegetable oil for frying For the Dipping Sauce: • 1/2 cup mayonnaise • 2 tablespoons honey • 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard • 1 teaspoon apple cider vinegar • A pinch of cayenne pepper (adjust to taste) Instructions: 1. Lay the chicken tenders out, season them lightly with salt and pepper and set aside. 2. In a shallow dish, combine the finely crushed @lays Sweet and Spicy Honey flavored potato chips, panko breadcrumbs, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, and a pinch of salt and pepper. 3. In another shallow dish, whisk together the eggs and milk. 4. Dredge each chicken tender first in flour, shaking off any excess, then dip it into the egg wash, and coat it thoroughly in the chip mixture. 5. Heat ~1” vegetable oil in a large pan to 325-350°F degrees. Fry the chicken, turning with tongs every 2-4 minutes and adjusting heat to maintain a steady temperature of 325°F, until crust is golden and the thickest part of the chicken registers 165°, about 8-10 minutes. Drain on paper towels to remove any excess oil. 6. To prepare the dipping sauce, mix all the ingredients for the dipping sauce in a small bowl. Adjust the cayenne pepper according to how spicy you like it. 7. To serve, arrange the cooked chicken tenders on a platter with the dipping sauce on the side.

We want to hear about it! 💌Head to @lays to share your special meal and story in the comments using #SwicyMarryMeMeal and #Sweepstakes for a chance to win $1,000 towards a dreamy Swicy™ date night! 🎉No purchase necessary. 18+. Ends 3/6 at 11:59 p.m. ET. Head to https://bit.ly/SwicyLaysTT for the full rules.    Swicy™ Chicken Tenders Ingredients: 1 lb (450g) chicken tenders 1 1/2 cups Lay's Sweet and Spicy Honey Flavored Potato Chips, crushed finely 1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs 1 teaspoon smoked paprika 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon onion powder 1 teaspoon cayenne powder Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste 2 large eggs 1 tablespoon milk 1/2 cup all-purpose flour Vegetable oil for frying For the Dipping Sauce: 1/2 cup mayonnaise 2 tablespoons honey 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard 1 teaspoon apple cider vinegar A pinch of cayenne pepper (adjust to taste) Instructions: 1. Lay the chicken tenders out, season them lightly with salt and pepper and set aside. 2. In a shallow dish, combine the finely crushed @lays Sweet and Spicy Honey flavored potato chips, panko breadcrumbs, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, and a pinch of salt and pepper.  3. In another shallow dish, whisk together the eggs and milk.  4. Dredge each chicken tender first in flour, shaking off any excess, then dip it into the egg wash, and coat it thoroughly in the chip mixture. 5. Heat ~1” vegetable oil in a large pan to 325-350°F degrees. Fry the chicken, turning with tongs every 2-4 minutes and adjusting heat to maintain a steady temperature of 325°F, until crust is golden and the thickest part of the chicken registers 165°, about 8-10 minutes. Drain on paper towels to remove any excess oil. 6. To prepare the dipping sauce, mix all the ingredients for the dipping sauce in a small bowl. Adjust the cayenne pepper according to how spicy you like it. 7. To serve, arrange the cooked chicken tenders on a platter with the dipping sauce on the side.

#ad NO BAKE OATMEAL CANDY COOKIES with @Quaker Oats  🎉🤍 It doesn’t get any easier or more delicious than these no bake cookies that come together in under 10 minutes. They’re a special family recipe that uses one of my fav pantry staples - Quaker Oats. Quaker has over 145 years of experience in milling trusted oat products. They’re great for the holidays but really make for a delicious snack any time of year! Hope you love them as much as we do! Ingredients: 3 cups Quaker Quick 1-Minute Oats ½ cup whole milk 1 cup granulated sugar 1 tsp vanilla extract ¼ cup margarine (it's very important to use actual margarine because it stays smooth and soft when it's room temp or cold. If you use butter the texture of the cookies is all wrong) ½ cup smooth peanut butter 5 Tbsp cocoa powder Unsweetened shredded coconut (for topping) Method: 1. In a medium pot combine margarine, milk, sugar, and vanilla extract. Over medium heat, bring the mixture to a rolling boil. Let cook for 1 minute until the sugar is dissolved and the ingredients are well combined. 2. Turn off the heat and carefully stir in the peanut butter, cocoa powder, and Quaker Quick 1-Minute Oats. Mix until everything is well combined. 3. Using a small cookie scoop or two spoons, quickly drop mounds of the cookie batter onto parchment paper. Shape and gently press down to form circles. Top with unsweetened shredded coconut and refrigerate for a minimum of 30 minutes. Enjoy! \#nobake #cookies #nobakecookies #oatmealcookies #cookierecipe #holidayfood #easyrecipes #cookielover #easyrecipesathome #oats #familyrecipes #simpleanddelicious #howto #foodstagram #recipevideo #yum

And of those rare moments when I have an idea to combine two media and it works out sooooo well!  I was thinking this combination of white acrylic ink + colored pencil would work fine, but the ethereal quality of the white acrylic ink made it even better than I could have anticipated.  Before acrylic inks I had used Winsor and Newton drawing inks, and I remember the white being sooooo watery and wimpy that never imagined a white ink would ever work well after that!  The white acrylic has a soft body to it that blended beautifully with the watercolor pencil. I’m seeing more and more that painting is more fun for me when I don’t use one paint media! xoxo Prof Lieu @claralieu  . . . . #acrylicink #acrylicinkspainting #acrylicinkart #acrylicinkonpaper #sweeneytodd #sweeneytoddthedemonbarberoffleetstreet #sweeneytoddfanart #sweeneytoddmusical #sweeneytoddbroadway #attendthetale

After purchasing a 1920s Spanish-style home in the Westwood neighborhood for her mother in 2019, the "Poor Things" star updated it with a new guesthouse and an expanded kitchen. Not only did Emma Stone just garner a Golden Globe win for her performance in the movie Poor Things, but the A-list actress also has decided to lighten her Los Angeles property portfolio. Records show Stone—who maintains a permanent residence in the Texas city of Austin—has stuck a nearly $4 million price tag on a relatively humble yet charming Spanish-style bungalow in the Comstock Hills area of Westwood that was long occupied by her mother. Though that’s around $1.7 million more than she paid for the place almost five years ago, back in spring 2019, Stone did extensively renovate the premises during her ownership. According to The Wall Street Journal, which first reported the listing, she expanded the kitchen, and added a one-bedroom guesthouse with its own kitchen and living room. A gated driveway is tucked off to the side of the creamy stucco and terracotta-roof structure, which is fronted by a brick walkway that passes through a grassy lawn before emptying out at a sage-green door that opens into the original tiled courtyard. Once inside, an entry foyer displaying a curving iron-railed staircase steps down to a light-filled living room adorned with a fireplace, built-in shelving and French doors leading outside. Among the other highlights: a formal dining area, plus a sitting room that connects to an eat-in kitchen outfitted with all-white wood cabinetry, a turquoise-hued range and farmhouse sink; and elsewhere is a primary bedroom hosting a stylish bath equipped with a vanity sporting a sink and dressing area, as well as a vintage clawfoot soaking tub and separate walk-in shower. Aside from her for-sale Westwood house and Texas mansion, Stone also maintains a posh New York City apartment. In 2022, she sold a midcentury ranch-style house directly overlooking Malibu’s Las Tunas Beach to David Cooley—longtime owner of The Abbey Food & Bar in West Hollywood—for $4.4 million, or nearly $1.2 million more than The Curse and Cruella star paid for the place back in 2018.#losangeles #housetour #emmastone #fyp #westwood #realestate #luxuryrealestate #la #architecture #celebrity #celebrityhomes

Weyes Blood’s most popular album Titanic Rising is an ethereal listen that feels like a warm blanket in times of pain. Weyes Blood’s vocals portray a motherly aura that beautifully pairs with her instrumentals, whether it’s folksy guitars or synths. She takes many influences from 70s soft rock, with inspiration from artists such as Joni Mitchell and the Carpenters. The lyrical content is very much all over the place. In the opening track, Weyes Blood looks back on the simpler times of childhood. She also discusses the difficulty of dating in today’s society, and climate change is a central theme with Titanic being used as a metaphor. This album is a standard for today’s soft rock, folk, and indie rock. Coming at the end of the 2010s, this is one of the best of the decade. #recommendations #review #aotd #music #fyp #album #weyesblood #softrock #indierock #folkrock

Snippet of ATC audio from the incident involving Alaska 1282 from Portland, OR (PDX) to Ontario, CA (ONT).  See below for my synopsis: Alaska Airlines CEO Ben Minicucci announced Friday evening that the airline’s fleet of Boeing 737-9 MAXs would be grounded pending emergency maintenance inspections.  This comes on the heels of an incident onboard Alaska Airlines Flight 1282 from Portland, OR (PDX) to Ontario, CA (ONT), where a plugged/inoperative door separated from the fuselage.  This caused a massive hole to open in an otherwise normal window NON-EXIT ROW seat.  The seat in question, 26A, remained inside the aircraft and was unoccupied at the time.  A small child was seated in the adjacent seat and a portion of his clothing was ripped from his body and sucked out of the aircraft.  No other injuries were reported among the 172 passengers and 6 crew members.  The jet was passing through 16,300-ft when the explosive decompression occurred.  This caused oxygen masks to fall and be worn by all onboard until the jet was below a breathable/comfortable altitude of 10,000-ft.  The aircraft diverted back to Portland, OR.  The aircraft, N701AL, was delivered new to the airline in October and began flying passengers December 7, 2023.  The new aircraft had experienced two separate pressurization issues on flights the day prior to the incident on January 4.  Both occurrences led Alaska Airlines to remove the aircraft from flying routes over water to Hawaii.  The airline elected to leave the jet in service since both occurrences happened on the ground and at the time did not indicate an immediate danger to flight operations.  The plugged door is found on all Boeing 737-9 MAX aircraft in the United States.  The door appears to be a normal window seat since it is not an active door and cannot be opened without major modification to the aircraft.  It is only used when airlines order the aircraft with the extra door configured for high capacity operations, unlike Alaska’s with 178 seats.  LionAir Indonesia has 221 all economy seats on the same type of aircraft, leading them to use the extra door.   #airline #planecrash #alaskaairlines #accident #aviation #alaska1282 #alaska #alaskaair

CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister interviews Gypsy Rose Blanchard, who was released from prison after serving eight years over a plot to kill her abusive mother, Dee Dee Blanchard. She pleaded guilty to second-degree murder in 2016 and admitted that she convinced her then-boyfriend to stab her mother to death. Blanchard was a victim of Munchausen syndrome by proxy, a rare disorder in which a caregiver feigns or exaggerates illness in someone to elicit attention or sympathy. She had spent her childhood and early adulthood believing she suffered from a host of serious ailments, including leukemia, muscular dystrophy and asthma. After the abuse she experienced at the hands of her mother came to light, Blanchard was sentenced to 10 years in prison and released two years early on December 28th. According to the Missouri Department of Corrections, she is expected to remain under parole supervision until June 2025. #cnn

I think about my great grandmother very, very often. My cousin and I would be in her house, running around the table while she sat in her chair. She let us run circles around her and laugh. The only thing she wanted from us, was to be happy. I’m not sure what I knew about her passing, as much as a 5 year old can understand I assume. My parents didn’t want to take me to the funeral, but my great aunt convinced them. As there were small crowds weeping with each other, probably talking about my mama d, my cousin and I ran around. We ran, we laughed, we were happy as we were oblivious to the situation around us. I hope she loved seeing that. I carry guilt as I can admit I’ve not been the happiest, and that was the only thing she wanted for my cousin and I. Grief hangs onto me tightly. The only way I can explain it, is as if there is a weighted blanket sewed with grief draped over my shoulders at all times. On worse days, it pins me down and I’m unable to move. On better days, I laugh and run like my mama d always loved to see, the blanket is light and there is grief, but it is more obviously love that I have not been able to share with her in a long time #web #webweaving #webweavingslideshow #webweavingpoetry #fyp #slideshow #writing #poetry #vent #slideshowpoetry #poetryslideshow #foryou

At last… multiple episodes of The Beatles Cartoon have been found in their original crisp high quality for the first time ever. Since bootleg VHS and DVDs have been around, The Beatles Cartoon always relied on pretty much the same recycled recordings from when MTV aired re-runs of the show in 1986-87, but unfortunately with even the best sources the quality was always fuzzy, oversaturated and lacked a lot of detail. Here is a direct comparison of the newly scanned original 1967 16mm print on top, and the previously highest quality version we ever had on the bottom. Somewhere, somehow, full broadcast episodes and sing-alongs have been discovered and scanned. They were released on a bootleg DVD in 2020 but made pretty much no noise until yesterday that The Beatles Videos on Youtube had brought to my attention that they found these scans and are de-interlacing them! And now for the first time ever digitally, we are able to see the true beauty and detail of the original show. For those who don’t know, much of the staff who worked on this cartoon series ended up shifting over to Yellow Submarine, and this cartoon was pretty much warmup for what that movie would become. This episode is Penny Lane, it was aired in 1967 as part of the Season 3 premire of the series, alongside my favorite episode Strawberry Fields.  This is something I have genuinely been waiting my entire life to see. Since before I could even read and write I can remember taking out the DVD of the fragile bootleg my dad got us and putting it right in the DVD player and watching them on repeat all day. I’ve been collecting the best versions of the series my whole life and to randomly be blessed with a bunch of full original quality scans of the series for the first time ever is just absolutely groundbreaking to me. Genuinely such an amazing way to send off the great year that 2023 was for Beatles fans, and a great gift to my childhood 🥹❤️ I will be sharing some more info on how they’re going to be released very soon… if you would like to view the raw scans you can find them via The Beatles Videos on youtube! I plan on remastering the audio myself, since whoever released these scans attempted to remaster it themselves but did a sloppy job unfortunately, where the songs can be out of sync and the sound effects are not correct (This is actually MY remastered audio in this clip!). My goal is to organize and share the series in a way that anyone can easily watch it in the best quality and sound! patience everyone! great stuff is coming, who knew we were ever going to get these! it really is something i never thought i’d see 🥲 LAST DAY OF 2023! Cookies, chopped, divided  Holiday sprinkle (optional)   Line 13x9-inch pan with foil, spray with cooking spray.   In large saucepan melt butter over low heat. Add 4 cups marshmallows and stir until completely melted. Remove from heat.   In a large bowl add marshmallow mixture, rice cereal, remaining marshmallows and ¾ of the Chips Ahoy! Cookies. BABY GIRL NAMESS 💁🏼‍♀️☘️🤍 Irish names often have deep historical and cultural roots, reflecting Ireland's rich heritage and mythology. They are known for their unique spellings and enchanting meanings, often derived from Gaelic, the indigenous language of Ireland. Many of these names have been passed down through generations, symbolizing various aspects of nature, folklore, and the island's history. Here are some beautiful Irish names for baby girls, along with their meanings: 1. **Aoife** (EE-fa) - Meaning "beauty" or "radiance," this name is associated with a legendary warrior princess in Irish folklore. 2. **Ciara** (KEE-ra) - Means "dark-haired" or "dark," reflecting a common characteristic in Irish heritage. 3. **Niamh** (NEEV or NEE-av) - Translates to "bright" or "radiant," a name associated with a figure from Irish mythology who lived in Tír na nÓg, the land of eternal youth. 4. **Saoirse** (SEER-sha) - Meaning "freedom" or "liberty," this name has gained popularity for its beautiful sound and its representation of the value of freedom. 5. **Aisling** (ASH-ling) - This name means "dream" or "vision" and is linked to a poetic genre in Irish literature that personifies Ireland. 6. **Fionnuala** (fin-NOO-la) - Derived from "fionn," meaning "fair," and "guala," meaning "shoulder." In legend, Fionnuala was turned into a swan for 900 years. 7. **Orla** (OR-la) - Meaning "golden princess," this name signifies beauty and royalty. 8. **Eimear** (EE-mer) - Known for embodying the six gifts of womanhood: beauty, voice, speech, needlework, wisdom, and chastity. 9. **Róisín** (ro-SHEEN) - A diminutive form of "róis," meaning "rose." It's a poetic way to name a child after the beauty of a rose. 10. **Caoimhe** (KEE-va or KWEE-va) - Means "gentle," "beautiful," or "precious." These names not only reflect the beauty of the Irish language but also carry with them stories and qualities that many find meaningful and inspiring.

Paul McCartney and Linda Eastman married on March 12, 1969, at the Marylebone Register Office in London. Their wedding was a relatively low-key affair compared to the frenzy often associated with Beatles-related events. It was a simple ceremony attended by close friends, family, and fellow Beatles bandmate, Ringo Starr, along with his wife, Maureen. Linda, an American photographer, met Paul at a club in London in 1967. Their relationship blossomed, and they became partners, sharing a deep love for each other. Linda’s support for Paul was evident not just in their personal life but also in his musical career, where she became an essential part of his band, Wings. Their union was marked by a genuine connection and shared interests, notably in animal rights and vegetarianism. Linda’s warmth and artistic talent complemented Paul’s creative pursuits, and they collaborated musically as well. She played keyboard and provided backing vocals for Wings, contributing to the band’s success. Their marriage lasted until Linda’s untimely death due to breast cancer in 1998. Paul often spoke fondly of their time together, highlighting the strength of their bond and the profound impact Linda had on his life, both personally and professionally. Their marriage remains a testament to love, partnership, and shared values enduring through the years. Follow me #historyinmemes for more!! #fyp #trave

This is why I insist that parents need support: they’re healing themselves, they’re healing their children, they often need to heal some parts of their marriage, and for many parents, they’re also supporting the physical + medical needs of THEIR OWN aging parents in the background! And ha, not to mention if they’re employed 🙃🙃 This is why family therapy is so important. We MUST begin by supporting the parents so that they can lead the healing of their family.  In the family therapy that I have been extensively trained in and practice, Emotionally Focused Family Therapy, we divide therapy into two phases: 1) parental openness 2) child vulnerability. We do not bring the child and parent together until the parent is open to the child’s needs and vulnerability. This protects the child from getting hurt further and sets the parent up to successfully work with their child.  I decided to role play this particular dyad 1) bc I see it in around 1/3rd of mom-daughter dyads that I’ve worked with 2) I also saw a good bit of this in the comment section of that viral post about parents taking accountability. More than one comment outright said, “they should validate me.” Lol.  My aim is not to attack mothers or fathers. It is to show where things go wrong and how that creates pain that then becomes a legacy of pain when we pass it down to our children. Family therapy involves examining our own relationships and experiences as children, identifying the pain that we have there, and working to heal both our own pain and that of our children’s. #ad NO BAKE OATMEAL CANDY COOKIES with @Quaker Oats  🎉🤍 It doesn’t get any easier or more delicious than these no bake cookies that come together in under 10 minutes. They’re a special family recipe that uses one of my fav pantry staples - Quaker Oats. Quaker has over 145 years of experience in milling trusted oat products. They’re great for the holidays but really make for a delicious snack any time of year! Hope you love them as much as we do! Ingredients: 3 cups Quaker Quick 1-Minute Oats ½ cup whole milk 1 cup granulated sugar 1 tsp vanilla extract ¼ cup margarine (it's very important to use actual margarine because it stays smooth and soft when it's room temp or cold. If you use butter the texture of the cookies is all wrong) ½ cup smooth peanut butter 5 Tbsp cocoa powder Unsweetened shredded coconut (for topping) Method: 1. In a medium pot combine margarine, milk, sugar, and vanilla extract. Over medium heat, bring the mixture to a rolling boil. Let cook for 1 minute until the sugar is dissolved and the ingredients are well combined. 2. Turn off the heat and carefully stir in the peanut butter, cocoa powder, and Quaker Quick 1-Minute Oats. Mix until everything is well combined. 3. Using a small cookie scoop or two spoons, quickly drop mounds of the cookie batter onto parchment paper. Shape and gently press down to form circles. Top with unsweetened shredded coconut and refrigerate for a minimum of 30 minutes. Enjoy! \#nobake #cookies #nobakecookies #oatmealcookies #cookierecipe #holidayfood #easyrecipes #cookielover #easyrecipesathome #oats #familyrecipes #simpleanddelicious #howto #foodstagram #recipevideo #yum

She said that she wanted to put the hospital bags into the car so that no matter where we are, we are ready to go to the hospital! She said that even if we were just going to get a snack, we should have everything packed and ready to go! I thought it was funny, but Kay knows better than me because I’ve never been through this before! 😂 I helped her get the bags in the car and she remembered one last thing! She plugged the car seat into the car and we were finally ready to travel without the risk of missing something at home that we would need in the hospital! Cookies, chopped, divided  Holiday sprinkle (optional)   Line 13x9-inch pan with foil, spray with cooking spray.   In large saucepan melt butter over low heat. Add 4 cups marshmallows and stir until completely melted. Remove from heat.   In a large bowl add marshmallow mixture, rice cereal, remaining marshmallows and ¾ of the Chips Ahoy! Cookies. Mix until evenly coated.    Press onto bottom of prepared pan. Top with remaining chopped cookies; press lightly into cereal mixture to secure. Cool completely.

#ad NO BAKE OATMEAL CANDY COOKIES with @Quaker Oats  🎉🤍 It doesn’t get any easier or more delicious than these no bake cookies that come together in under 10 minutes. They’re a special family recipe that uses one of my fav pantry staples - Quaker Oats. Quaker has over 145 years of experience in milling trusted oat products. They’re great for the holidays but really make for a delicious snack any time of year! Hope you love them as much as we do! Ingredients: 3 cups Quaker Quick 1-Minute Oats ½ cup whole milk 1 cup granulated sugar 1 tsp vanilla extract ¼ cup margarine (it's very important to use actual margarine because it stays smooth and soft when it's room temp or cold. If you use butter the texture of the cookies is all wrong) ½ cup smooth peanut butter 5 Tbsp cocoa powder Unsweetened shredded coconut (for topping) Method: 1. In a medium pot combine margarine, milk, sugar, and vanilla extract. Over medium heat, bring the mixture to a rolling boil. Let cook for 1 minute until the sugar is dissolved and the ingredients are well combined. 2. Turn off the heat and carefully stir in the peanut butter, cocoa powder, and Quaker Quick 1-Minute Oats. Mix until everything is well combined. 3. Using a small cookie scoop or two spoons, quickly drop mounds of the cookie batter onto parchment paper. Shape and gently press down to form circles. Top with unsweetened shredded coconut and refrigerate for a minimum of 30 minutes.
